 \"from\": 84, \"to\": 93}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic and world championships gold\", \"from\": 110, \"to\": 146}, {\"ngram\": \"her sometimes goofy self\", \"from\": 160, \"to\": 184}, {\"ngram\": \"more history\", \"from\": 198, \"to\": 210}, {\"ngram\": \"coach Cecile Landi\", \"from\": 237, \"to\": 255}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles dazzled in winning four gold medals at the 2016 Rio de Janeiro Olympics, but her campaign at the pandemic-delayed Tokyo Games was cut short as she dealt with the debilitating spatial awareness condition gymnasts call \\\"the twisties\\\".\", \"from\": 263, \"to\": 501, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Biles\", \"from\": 263, \"to\": 268}, {\"ngram\": \"four gold medals\", \"from\": 288, \"to\": 304}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2016 Rio de Janeiro Olympics\", \"from\": 308, \"to\": 340}, {\"ngram\": \"her campaign\", \"from\": 346, \"to\": 358}, {\"ngram\": \"the pandemic-delayed Tokyo Games\", \"from\": 362, \"to\": 394}, {\"ngram\": \"the debilitating spatial awareness condition gymnasts\", \"from\": 427, \"to\": 480}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"the twisties\", \"from\": 486, \"to\": 499}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After a lengthy break, marriage to NFL player Jonathan Owens, and with a commitment to her mental wellness part of the process, Biles has returned in dominant form.\", \"from\": 503, \"to\": 667, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 538, \"end\": 541, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Football_League\", \"score\": 0.9999910872367503, \"rank\": 7.488562235152575e-06, \"text\": \"NFL\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Football_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Football_League\"}, {\"begin\": 549, \"end\": 563, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonathan_Owens\", \"score\": 0.9999928980971419, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jonathan Owens\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonathan_Owens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonathan_Owens\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a lengthy break\", \"from\": 509, \"to\": 524}, {\"ngram\": \"marriage\", \"from\": 526, \"to\": 534}, {\"ngram\": \"a commitment\", \"from\": 574, \"to\": 586}, {\"ngram\": \"her mental wellness part\", \"from\": 590, \"to\": 614}, {\"ngram\": \"the process\", \"from\": 618, \"to\": 629}, {\"ngram\": \"Biles\", \"from\": 631, \"to\": 636}, {\"ngram\": \"dominant form\", \"from\": 653, \"to\": 666}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She won five medals at the 2023 World Championships in Antwerp, remaining unbeaten in World Championships all-around and floor competition with her sixth titles in each event.\", \"from\": 669, \"to\": 844, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 724, \"end\": 731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antwerp\", \"score\": 0.9999293029501124, \"rank\": 7.067584525978805e-05, \"text\": \"Antwerp\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antwerp\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antwerp\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"five medals\", \"from\": 677, \"to\": 688}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2023 World Championships\", \"from\": 692, \"to\": 720}, {\"ngram\": \"remaining unbeaten\", \"from\": 733, \"to\": 751}, {\"ngram\": \"World Championships all-around and floor competition\", \"from\": 755, \"to\": 807}, {\"ngram\": \"her sixth titles\", \"from\": 813, \"to\": 829}, {\"ngram\": \"each event\", \"from\": 833, \"to\": 843}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Antwerp, she successfully performed her Yurchenko double pike vault, now known as the Biles II - the fifth skill named for her as the first woman to complete it in international competition.\", \"from\": 846, \"to\": 1039, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 849, \"end\": 856, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antwerp\", \"score\": 0.9999293029501124, \"rank\": 7.067584525978805e-05, \"text\": \"Antwerp\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.